25/03/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- NATO Secretary General Jaap De Hoop Scheffer met with Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano this week and acknowledged the important role Tirana plays in the region, according to local media reports Thursday (24 March). Nano was attending a meeting of the NATO Council of Ambassadors in Brussels. De Hoop Scheffer said reform progress in the defence sector is solid and instrumental to Albania's future membership in NATO. He also praised Tirana's role in NATO peacekeeping operations.
In other news, Albanian local media reported on Friday that Tirana fully supports new Kosovo Prime Minister Bajram Kosumi. In turn, Kosumi said he plans to visit Tirana soon. (Albanian Daily News - 25/03/05)
